The course covers all the stages necessary for conducting empirical research. Students learn to plan research, formulate research questions and hypotheses. Students learn the basics of data collection and processing and their presentation. The goal is to complete a master's thesis and, for a longer period, to be ready to guide future students in conducting their research at school.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To support students in completing their master's theses. The participants of the course are able to plan and carry out research.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The student knows: 1. basic principles of scientific research, stages of research 2. the principles of the quantitative data analysis   3. principles of supervising students' research at school The student is able to: 1.  present, and interpret scientific articles in the field of mathematics education 2.  to plan and carry out a master's thesis, 3.  help students in their research at school.
